\chapter*{Book Description}
\begin{description}
\item [Title:] Power Electronics: Principles \& Applications
\item [Author:] J. M. Jacob
\item [Publisher:] Cengage Learning, New Delhi
\item [Edition:] 4
\item [Year:] 2009
\item [ISBN:] 9788131501184
\end{description}

\newpage
\vspace*{3cm}
Scilab numbering policy used in this document and the relation to the above book.
\begin{description}
\item[Exa] Example (Solved example)
\item[Eqn] Equation (Particular equation of the above book)
\item[AP] Appendix to Example(Scilab Code that is an Appednix to a particular Example of the above book)
\end{description}
For example, Exa~3.51 means solved example 3.51 of this book. Sec~2.3 means a scilab code whose theory is explained in Section 2.3 of the book.

